parts.text: "I have been having thoughts of harm."
"Im having trouble managing my daily life"
"How to handle anxiety"
"Medication for depression"
"Anxiety meds"
"I am anxious and need help"
"My anxiety has been acting up lately"
"How do I relieve depression?"
"i am having thoughts of suicide"
"I am thinking about killing myself"
"going to kill myself"
"I think I might do something to hurt myself"
"I'm afraid I'm going to hurt myself"
"I've been cutting myself, it's the only way I can feel better"
"I haven't left my house in weeks, and I've stopped responding to texts and calls, I don't want anyone to find me."
"I'm feeling overwhelmed and I quit my job suddenly. Now I don't know what to do next."
"I keep getting into arguments with my family and say things I don't mean. I regret it every time, but I can't seem to stop myself."
"I ate an entire cake last night without thinking. I was stressed and now feel guilty."
"I emptied my savings account to buy something I thought would make me happy, but now I'm worried about my finances."
"I dropped out of my class today because I felt like I couldn't handle it anymore."
"I feel very strange. I'm having feelings of impulsiveness, like one moment I need to act immediately without thinking, and the next, I feel overwhelmed by regret or confusion about what I just did."
"I may have acted too quickly and now I regret my actions. However, I find myself doing this a lot. Is there a problem with me?"
"I sometimes think irrationaly and incapble of controlling my actions. Is this normal?"
"My son cannot control his emotions. He easily gets angry and impulsive. Do you have any idea on where I can get help?"
"I threw my pills away. I'm done taking them. They don't do anything for me."
"I experienced racing thoughts last night and couldn't sleep till 4am, I have been taking clozapam since Nov 22nd, Levoflaxin since yesterday"
"I'm shaking. anxiety is running my body right now "
"He is super restless"
"I stopped taking my antidepressants because it was giving me too many side effects. Now I feel very depressed and down, to the point where I'm not sure what to do next. "
"I had a few drinks after taking my antidepressants, and now I feel my heart beating irregularly."
"I stopped taking my painkillers cold turkey, and now I have chills and body aches"
"I have been experiencing weird symptoms since discontinuing my metformin."
"not sure what is going on with me. I'm type 2 diabetic and for the past 5 days I haven't been able to take my medicine "
"I took some drugs last night and I feel very confused."
"I stopped drinking and now I'm constantly vomitting and have black stools."
"I am going through alcohol withdrawal."
"Skin feels cool and clammy. I can't stop sweating after taking this medication."
"It takes all I have to do the simplest things. I’ve gone months without showering, I’ve woken up and lied in bed for the next 8 hours straight staring at the ceiling"

"I don't know what's wrong with me. At times I can be really happy, excited, I'll talk fast, and I want to do things. But lately I've been staying up way later and sleeping too much. I don't hang out with friends, I don't really have them. I feel nothing, worthless. I want to do nothing, I have no interest in anything. All I usually do is stay in my room. I want to be happy, I want to be nice. What's wrong with me?"
"I feel like im in an emotional roller coaster."
"I have a history of manic/depressive disorder and I feel very low right now."
"My daughter hit me multiple times."
"I couldn't control my daughter. She is having a really hard time trying to control herself."
"I've previously made attempts to harm someone."
"I'm not suicidal but we have a gun in the home."
"I have no energy to do anything."
"I have been extremely angry lately."
"Someon very close to me has passed away and now I am in a dark place."
"I pushed away everyone I know, and now I’m sitting alone in the dark, wondering if I should even be here anymore."
"I’ve been isolating myself, and now I’m thinking about ending it all because no one will even notice I’m gone."
"I’ve been avoiding my friends for weeks, and now I just want to disappear completely."
"I don't trust my family or friends. I think they are plotting against me. Maybe they want to put me away into a mental institution."
"I've cutoff communication with everyone I know. I feel alone and lonely."
"Nobody cares about me. I stopped hanging out with my friends and family. They just wouldn't care if I drop dead."
"I feel worthless and I'm just no good to anybody. Not even to my family."
"My baby won't stop crying and I just can't take it anymore. I'm having thoughts of hurting my baby."
"I can't bring myself to talk to anyone."
"I have been having a really hard time being around people"

"It is very hard.  I also hav stage 4 breast cancer, and see my oncologist every 3 months, but its' very tough to deal with, and I assume the part of the problem is that I'm trying to self medicate with alcohol.  I know that is not good.  But I am very stressed out."

"I feel like am not in control of my drinking.  I have a job, I am married and a good mom, but i drink wine every day.  It's too much, I know.  There is no violence or danger.  But I know it has hurt my marriage and some of my friendships."

"I believe I’m experiencing PTSD and panic attacks. It’s becoming difficult to maintain a job because of the disruptions I feel are taking place while I’m clocked in. It feels like my chest is closing up, my breathing becomes heavy and audible, more like a grunting noise. My eyes become very wide and I start to sob uncontrollably.  I want to find a therapist and PCP to help guide me with the right medication or therapy steps. I feel like I am suffering from the moment I wake up and do not have a steady sleep pattern because of what I’m experiencing. Im not quite sure how to take the next step but I need help in order to maintain my job and be able to function."
"The past few days it has gotten much worse but the last time i can remember feeling any sense of  happiness was early 2018"
"The past few days in particular I haven’t been able to interact w/ people and I haven’t eaten in about three days because i just can’t bring myself to do anything but cry and attempt to sleep"
"just don't want to feel like this anymore. seems nothing is ever right for me all stres and worry"
"my anxiety and my stress is already through the roof and this is just making my conditions worse"
"I’m going through a very traumatic period in our life and it’s effecting both of us physically and mentally"
"I can't stop crying"
"I have a firearm in the house I could use on myself"
"I feel like killing myself"
"I tried to hurt myself"
"I just feel like the world would be a beter place if I didn't exist"
"I'm so tired of everything"
"This has been going on for too long"
"I'm scared and feel alone and may hurt myself"
"No one cares what happens to me"
"I don't care if I exist"
"I'm going to get wasted"
"Nothing brings me peace"
"It's all my fault"
"I feel so hopeless"
"I'm so ashamed"
"I'm at the end of my rope"
"I've written letters to everyone"
"I feel worthless"
"Nothing is ever going to get better"
"I am thinking of killing myself"
